SIMPLE: everglade
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Everglade
<hw>Ev`er*glade</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>A swamp or low
tract of land inundated with water and interspersed with hummocks, or
small islands, and patches of high grass; <as>as, the
<ex>everglades</ex> of Florida</as>.</def> <mark>[U. S.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><note>⟦hand⟧ When used in the United States without qualification,
the word <ex>Everglades</ex> is understood to refer to the Everglades of
southern Florida.</note>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Evergreen</ent>⟦br⟧
